include ../../tlMatter.pug
if docLang === "EN"
  mixin tl(tlText)
    if tlText != null
      +inlineTl("EN", tlText)
    else
      +inlineTl("EN")
        block
    
  mixin tlDb(key)
    case key
      when "teidealNaCaibidle"
        | The Adjective
      when "4-title"
        | #[+renderKey("Caibidil", { getFromCommon: true })] 4 | #[+renderKey("teidealNaCaibidle")]
      when "4-1-title"
        | The Attributive Adjective
      when "4-1-1-p"
        | The adjectives are divided into three declensions.
      when "4-1-2-p"
        | The adjective is only declined when it is used as an attributive adjective.
      when "4-1-3-p"
        | The form of the attributive adjective depends on gender, case and number of the noun that it is qualifying and on the declension of the adjective itself. See #[+link("./chapter9.html", "Chapter 9")] for rules on using adjectives with numbers.
      when "4-2-title"
        | Gender, Case and Number of the Attributive Adjective
      when "4-2-1-p"
        | The qualifying adjective agrees with the noun in gender, case and number. When there is a series of nouns, the adjective agrees with the final noun, e.g., #[i mná agus fir ghnaíúla]; #[i peann, páipéar agus bileog ghorm] #[+tl blue pen, paper and sheet]. When a series of adjectives follows a single noun, every adjective agrees with the noun, e.g., #[i ailt shuimiúla thábhachtacha fhada] #[+tl interesting, important, long articles].
      when "4-2-1-p-sample1"
        | The #[b lovely] women and men came in.
      when "4-2-1-p-sample2"
        | The #[b lovely] men and women came in.
      when "4-2-1-p-sample3"
        | She had a #[b blue] skirt, coat and scarf on.
      when "4-2-1-p-sample4"
        | There are #[b big, wild] cats in the zoo.
      when "4-2-2-a-p"
        | In the singular &mdash;
      when "4-2-2-a-i-p"
        | when there is a masculine noun, the adjective that qualifies it is not lenited, e.g., #[i an fear beag] #[+tl the small man]; #[i ag an bhfear beag] #[+tl at the small man]; except in the vocative case and in the genitive case e.g., #[i a fhir bhig] #[+tl O small man]; #[i hata an fhir bhig] #[+tl the hat of the small man].
      when "4-2-2-a-ii-p"
        | if the Lenition System (see #[+link("./chapter1.html#sec_1_7", "1.7")]) is in use, the adjective that qualifies the masculine noun is lenited in the dative case if the article goes with that noun, e.g., #[i ag an fhear bheag] #[+tl at the small man].
      when "4-2-2-b-p"
        | In the singular, when there is a feminine noun, the adjective that qualifies it is lenited in all the cases, e.g., #[i an bhean bheag] #[+tl the small woman]; #[i a bhean bheag] #[+tl O small woman]; #[i ag an mbean bheag] #[+tl at the small woman]; except in the genitive case, e.g., #[i hata na mná bige] #[+tl the hat of the small woman].
      when "4-2-3-p"
        | #[+link("./chapter9.html", "Chapter 9")] provides an illustration of the attributive adjective when a number precedes the noun being qualified.
      when "4-2-4-title"
        | Lenition of an Attributive Adjective in the Singular
      when "4-2-4-p"
        | An adjective is either left bare or inflected based on the gender and case of the noun it is qualifying. The contexts are shown in the table below. See the discussion of adjective declension (#[+link("#sec_4_3", "4.3")]) for information on form change (other than lenition) of the adjective itself.
      when "lenition"
