      when "no-lenition"
        | no lenition
      when "Table4A-caption"
        | Lenition of an Attributive Adjective in the Singular
      when "Table4A-col1"
        | The Case
      when "Table4A-col2"
        | Singular Masculine Noun
      when "Table4A-col3"
        | Singular Feminine Noun
      when "Table4A-row1"
        | Nominative and Accusative
      when "Table4A-row2"
        | Vocative
      when "Table4A-row3"
        | Dative*
      when "Table4A-row4"
        | Genitive
      when "Table4A-footnote"
        | But see #[+link("./chapter1.html#sec_1_7", "1.7")] The Lenition System
      when "4-2-5-title"
        | Lenition of Attributive Adjective in the Plural
      when "4-2-5-p"
        | In the plural, the initial consonant of the adjective is lenited if the plural noun starts with a slender consonant, as in the table below (see also #[+link("./chapter10.html#sec_10_3_1", "10.3.1")]).
      when "Table4B-col1-main"
        | Lenition
      when "Table4B-col2-main"
        | Without Lenition
      when "Table4B-col1-sub"
        | Noun that starts with a slender consonant in the plural
      when "Table4B-col2-sub"
        | Noun that starts with a broad consonant or vowel in the plural
      when "4-3-title"
        | Declensions of the Adjectives
      when "4-3-1-p"
        | The form of the adjective is the same in the nominative, accusative and dative singular cases, and the form of the adjective is the same in the nominative, accusative and dative plural cases.
      when "4-3-2-p"
        | In the genitive plural case &mdash;
      when "4-3-2-a-p"
        | if the noun is a strong plural, the same form of the adjective is used as is used in the nominative plural case:
      when "4-3-2-a-sample-row1"
