      when "4-3-2-a-sample-row2"
        | Genitive plural
      when "4-3-2-a-sample1"
        | I like the #[b great] poets.
      when "4-3-2-a-sample2"
        | I like the #[b great] poems of the poets.
      when "4-3-2-b-p"
        | if the noun is a weak plural, the same form of adjective is used as is used in the nominative singular case:
      when "4-3-2-b-sample-row1"
        | Nominative singular
      when "4-3-2-b-sample-row2"
        | Genitive plural
      when "4-3-2-b-sample1"
        | The #[b local] authority publishes a report every year.
      when "4-3-2-b-sample2"
        | The reports of the #[b local] authorities were published.
      when "4-3-3-a-p"
        | An adjective in the masculine vocative is not lenited or inflected if it is a nickname or metaphorical in meaning.
      when "4-3-3-a-p-sample1"
        | How are you, #[b little father]?
      when "4-3-3-a-p-sample2"
        | #[b Faithful brother], I knew very well it was you.
      when "4-3-3-a-p-sample3"
        | #[b Fragrant mouth], we won&rsquo;t be happy together.
      when "4-3-3-a-p-sample4"
        | How are you, #[b white son]?
