      when "4-3-6-p-sample3"
        | They are not #[b very quiet] children.
      when "4-3-7-p"
        | The adjective is neither inflected nor lenited if it is part of a multi-word adjectival phrase, e.g., #[i athnuachan saor in aisce] #[+tl free renewal]; #[i tuarascáil cothrom le dáta] #[+tl up-to-date report].
      when "4-3-7-p-sample1"
        | She is a #[b prominent] woman in the field of science.
      when "4-3-7-p-sample2"
        | The author of the #[b up-to-date] report gave the presentation.
      when "4-3-8-p"
        | The form of the singular genitive is described under each separate declension.
      when "4-4-title"
        | The First Declension
      when "4-4-p"
        | Included in this declension are adjectives ending with a consonant, broad or slender, aside from adjectives ending with #[i -úil] and certain adjectives ending with #[i -ir] (see #[+link("#sec_4_5", "4.5")]).
      when "4-4-1-title"
        | Form of the Genitive Singular
      when "4-4-1-a-title"
        | Masculine
      when "4-4-1-a-i-p"
        | If the adjective ends with a broad consonant, the consonant is palatalized as it would be done with a noun in the First Declension (see #[+link("./chapter2.html#sec_2_2_2", "2.2.2")]).
