      when "4-11-p"
        | An predicative adjective is an adjective that qualifies the noun as predicate or as part of a predicate, e.g., #[i Nach deas é?] #[+tl Isn&rsquo;t it nice?] ; #[i Tá an aimsir fuar] #[+tl The weather is cold]. The predicative adjective is not inflected or lenited.
